{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "New rules on online gossip sites",
        "additional_details": "It\u2019s about every child being spoken about online without consent. Every mum being shamed. Every person scared to post on social media because of bullying. We consider such sites to be hate forums\u2014and ask the government to protect all people from this toxic online culture. It\u2019s for every person who\u2019s been discussed without consent, mocked for their appearance, or made to feel unsafe. It's for the children who will one day read those comments. I\u2019m standing up not just for myself\u2014but for everyone.",
        "background": "Strengthen rules on online gossip sites. Require identity checks for users and takedowns of abuse within 24 hours, alongside the existing regulation in the Online Safety Act.",
